# AUDIT VERIFICATION SUMMARY (2025-12-02)
# ==============================================================================
# This diagram has been comprehensively audited against the C++ codebase.
# 
# VERIFIED COMPONENTS (All Accurate):
# ✓ Python Bindings: PyExecutor<BatchExecutor>, PyExecutor<StreamingExecutor>, pybind11
# ✓ Executor Interfaces: IPipelineExecutor (pipeline_executor.hpp:57)
# ✓ Executor Implementations: BatchExecutor, StreamingExecutor (both implement IPipelineExecutor)
# ✓ Configuration: ExecutorConfig : SignalConfig, StageConfig, ProcessingStats
# ✓ Builder Pattern: PipelineBuilder (pipeline_builder.hpp)
# ✓ Stage Interface: IProcessingStage (processing_stage.hpp:153)
# ✓ Stage Implementations: WindowStage, FFTStage, MagnitudeStage (all implement IProcessingStage)
# ✓ Stage Factory: StageFactory with create() and create_default_pipeline()
# ✓ Streaming: RingBuffer<T> template (ring_buffer.hpp:57) - lock-free, pinned memory
# ✓ CUDA Resources: CudaStream, CudaEvent, DeviceBuffer<T>, PinnedHostBuffer<T>, CufftPlan
# ✓ CUDA Kernels: apply_window_kernel, magnitude_kernel (fft_wrapper.cu)
# ✓ FFT Integration: cuFFT via CufftPlan wrapper
# ✓ Profiling: NVTX ScopedRange, macros (nvtx.hpp)
# ✓ Utilities: window_utils, signal_utils namespaces
# 
# DESIGN PATTERNS DOCUMENTED:
# - Strategy Pattern: IPipelineExecutor, IProcessingStage interfaces
# - Factory Pattern: StageFactory for stage creation
# - Builder Pattern: PipelineBuilder for pipeline composition
# - RAII Pattern: All CUDA resource wrappers (move-only, unique ownership)
# - Pimpl Idiom: BatchExecutor::Impl, StreamingExecutor::Impl (hide CUDA deps)
# 
# FILES VERIFIED:
# - cpp/bindings/bindings.cpp (Python bindings)
# - cpp/include/ionosense/core/pipeline_executor.hpp (IPipelineExecutor)
